'm wrong (and I'm sure someone will *insert smile*) that what is being said is that your skill (i prefer the word knowledge) goes up the more diverse the raids you have performed in.  And in suit, the more diverse the raids and simply the more no. of high end raids you have been on, the better your chances are to come away with high end equipment.  So if the statement was ... in general, the more different high end raids you've participated in, the higher your knowledge (skills) will be and in turn the better gear you will have.<br>
<br>
I think that what stirred up the commotion is two-fold. One in the over simplification with saying the better gear you have the more skilled you are.  It can easly be seen in different ways, depending upon what side of the track you live on.  Also, it implies that everyone with lots of great gear is skilled.  Well, I've met some who have had high end gear that I wouldn't necessarily call them knowledgeable and some at level 50 still in raw silk that I would consider skilled.  <br>
<br>
Just my perspective<br>
