<br>
When I said,&quot;I've gotten really tired of the overall attitude of people who don't play the high end game and blame US, the uber guilds for their inadequacies.&quot; What i should have said is this,&quot;I'm tired of getting flak for being in a guild that does tough shit with a low amount of people, and getting crapped on by a person who didn't get around to it yet.&quot; Yes, this means people who haven't seen or done a zone and give me shit because Hoss &quot;ruined&quot; it for them. VI set the script in place, VI has the recapture quest (broken) so who do you blame? Hell, I don't even have an ST key....<br>
<br>
I mentioned not hating the players but hating the game instead. Someone mentioned that it was hogwash. Was I off by much? Let me explain. Where to start besides the small stuff like class imbalance and broken quests? Perhaps the biggest flaw of the game is the spawn times. It's meant to slow the game down. All it does it make it competitive for people to &quot;race&quot; to spawns.<br>
<br>
The IGB has not been around since D-Ro was made, in fact it wasn't around when I joined Hoss. Ask yourselves something, if the IGB were still around in full force, and was never &quot;defiled&quot; how long would it take before we had 10 guilds on rotation? 20? 30? As stated before, spawn times reduced the amount of loot distributed out to a population per server. In a given month with no patches (yeah right!) Nagafen can be killed 4 times. Now, take your guild_X and you need Naggy and his phat l3wt for your guild or even for yourself, and figure out how many times you get that spawn each month. With 10 guilds on rotation you won't see that mob for how long? Thought so. In the cycle of life, there is birth, life and death. I haven't really seen any of the &quot;uber&quot; guilds die out. We just keep getting more and more bored level 60 players who want to go kill stuff and the amount to kill gets smaller and smaller. Survival of the fittest? Not quite. Survival of the earliest maybe.<br>
<br>
Where was I? Oh yeah....<br>
<br>
Have I personally wronged you? Have I trained you? (besides my little lost excursion through fungus grove, I'm sorry about that) Most likely the answer is no. What has my guild done for a smaller guild? Well what do you consider as far as help, and how many people from Hoss does it take to be considered helping? I spent many hours helping CR people in Fear. I've travelled across a dozen zones to rez people with nothing but a thank you in it for me. I've buffed 50 people or more for a naggy raid before along with CR of that raid and many others. You say rez's and C2 doesn't count? Whatever. I've given items to new players, plat to others. I have buffed low level groups out of the kindness of my heart. No payback. No thought of anything in return. I've refused payments from people that I've rezzed. Where do I need to go to get in the graces of other players? As stated before, I play to have fun.<br>
<br>
Kaludram- I've known you quite a while indeed. To see what I say about my guild's behavior? They acted in accordance with the wishes of the members of Hoss, whole or in part. Did we release the Sleeper to cut off Primal flow? Not at all. We did it to do it. Quick question: When you buy a video game, do you play it to beat it? In essence releasing the Sleeper was sort of beating the game. To a point of course. It was put in to be difficult and hard and it was done. You are right when I say,&quot;Stop crying.&quot; It is JUST a game after all.<br>
<br>
Anyways, the Sleeper is supposed to wake up. Why put it in game if it isn't supposed to happen? Sure the recapture quest is broken (refer to broken quest comment) and it makes people upset that they can't get primal anymore. I can understand why you are upset. You do know it still drops right? Just not as frequently. If/When VI decides to fix that quest, guess what? You'll have warders again. You'll have primal flowing once more. It's just a delay. Do you have the needed keyed people for ST? Go farm the 3 mobs that drop primal.<br>
<br>
Do I feel that what Hoss did was selfish and greedy? Not in the slightest. Do I have any primal? Nope, don't even have a key to get in. The selfish and greedy act would have been to get all our members outfitted with keys and primal, and their twinks. We didn't do that though. We just enabled a script that was put in game. 'Nuff said.<br>
<br>
As far as the intent of the original post, I was mad when I wrote it. I had logged into the game as always and spammed with hateful remarks on how selfish, greedy and insensitive I'd been. I wasn't even there. These remarks coming from people I knew, people I liked, people I actually talked to on a daily basis. Received several from complete strangers because they saw the guild tag. If you ask me, it sounds a lot like I'm a victim of blind harrassment and you are a victim of poor game design. <br>
<br>
If my post offended you, let it roll off your back. I won't apologize for any of it, it's not something to apologize for anymore than the flames directed at me. Opinions are like assholes, everyone has one and they all stink. Hope you have a good gaming experience and my guild doesn't ruin it for you.<br>
<br>
Fizbain Xavious<br>
59th Templar of HOSS<br>
Druzzil Ro<br>
