o it comes down to loot.  Now, even if the Sleeper was not released, the recent decision of Vindication to go FFA pretty much guarantees that either they or someone else would be in there all the time.  Would any up-and-coming guild really have a chance to get primal anyway?  Now there are fewer mobs that drop it, making it much more rare, so will the uber guilds continue to take the time?<br>
<br>
Hopefully the quest to recapture the Sleeper WILL get fixed soon, but in the meantime, maybe some of the other high-level zones will see a bit more activity.  It's kinda like the abundance of epic weapons -- primal stuff is not supposed to be common.  Perhaps the decision to release the Sleeper seems wrong to some, and I'm not saying that it was considerate to do it, but it's not worth the attention that it's being given, either to protest or defend a deed that has been done.<br>
<br>
And as for FFA, there were already a number of mid-level guilds who were NOT recognizing any reservation systems, either stating this, or just waltzing in to grab mobs.  It's not anything new, not even to this server, but it's just getting attention now that an established uber guild has openly stated that FFA is their policy.  I think people are just now becoming vocal about their concerns because of the &quot;I could happen to me!&quot; mentality, while some of us have been feeling the effects of FFA for months.  <br>
<br>
Those of you who have respected the reservation system(s) should continue to do so.  Those who do NOT honor such a system aren't going to start any time soon, and the playground doesn't need more bullies if you ask me.  Those of us who are willing to get along nicely should stick to it, and those who choose not to can fight with each other, each trying to one-up the other.<br>
<br>
