<br>
I don't remember where I read it, but someone at verant commented on how some players will never be happy (in response to a comment about awakening the sleeper and server being in an uproar). That statement has some merit, but at the same time they cannot deny the fact that at their first attempt at something like this, they made some serious mistakes. Ignoring this and blaming the players will not help them learn to do better in the future. They made an encounter that was supposed to be fun to do, but instead players wanted to farm the items instead. The fact that they put stuff on the warders that will never drop again, or will not drop nearly as much, is pretty ridiculous. The fact it makes people NOT want to do their neat little story should say a heck of a lot to them.  <br>
<br>
I think the best way to think about all this, is to just consider it a GM event without needing GMs. It is a shame if you miss it, but it doesn't take away from your eq experience. I have missed alot of neat GM events, but I got over it, and I got over this.<br>
<br>
In a way it is a shame it took this long to do it. The primal weapons that should rightfully be rare and special (because of the fact it is from a unique event, and because of how powerful), were relatively easy to get and became a sort of standard. Setting this standard and then just taking it away is wrong. How many GM event items shape the way the game is played forever afterwards?<br>
<br>
If these weapons were truly balanced in verants eyes, then if anything they should have been extremely rare before the sleeper was awakened, and then had drops the same as they are now for after being awakened. Reward the players for actually doing the storyline/quest, and maybe they will want to do it. If you could get your epic by only doing half of the quest, would you finish the quest anyway? How many people do quests they know are broken?<br>
<br>
Oh well, sort of lost my train of thought now. This is just my opinion, you don't have to agree. Heck I might change my mind next week, or tomorrow even! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I have no real experience with any &quot;uber&quot; encounters, the baddest mob I ever helped kill was maestro, and my only experience with primal weapons was seeing someone's primal proc in a group a few times, which I might not have even noticed if it didn't prevent my buffs from sticking. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uwoolhead.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Woolhead</A> at: 1/28/02 11:30:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ukaludramaderlas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaludram Aderlas</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.fortunecity.com/samslade/shadcon/Images/minisc.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 296<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(1/29/02 1:06:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=98>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To those who hate uber guilds...</span><hr size=1> Sirensa, predominate opinion on the server is that your guild as a whole looks like an ass.  Well done.  You got your theoretical job by backstabbing theoretically.  <br>
